                  </hi>. I live in Church-street, St. Giles's and am the wife of Edward Gardiner. The prisoner had lodged in my house—I missed the sheets and blankets—I went after her, and asked her for the things—she said she knew nothing about them—she went to the fire, took off the kettle, and threw something into the fire—I told the officer who was with me, and he went to the fire, took off the kettle again, and snatfched off this hus-wife, which contained the duplicates—these are my articles.</p>
